title: Love poem
author: deimante
text: when a heart is broken.  the love dissaperars.  and if there is no love there is no life.   as a tear falls down a  face.  it kills your soul and your heart stops beating until you find love again.   you beg him to come back.  but he disagrees.  you throw the pain back to him  but no matter what you do the pain still comes back.   life is hard and sometimes easy but mostly your life  is miserable without love.   you die without trustness  and without hope but your  feelings about him never  change.   your beauty surprises me.  as you hug me all day long.  i press you very tight against  myself.  great passion fills my inner  being.   i'm caught in your embrace.  your heart controls my soul.   the touch of your lips,  heaven.  forever froze my time,  all else fades into fades into nothing.   i hate you.  i wish to tear you away from me.  this tumor that clings to my chest.   the thing that makes me ache.  you bring my mind unwanted pain.   i will always hate you  and always love you but my feelings will always stay the same.

sitting there sobbing deeply for hours,   but here is how it all started,    50 years ago when autumn skies were red and orange,   the corn stalks grew 10 feet tall,   when sword grass was sharp as am now sir james,  i am a knight yehayâ”,    and raphael became part of a caravan pack  riding on a pack of camels on the desert oasis  in the arabian peninsula,   visiting syria,   living a life of to be loyal to your king,  â‘king richard   the lion heart. â”  king phillip then said,  â“shut up knight. â” sir james said â‘i can kill you if i wanted to,  king phillip replied â“you donâ’t stand a chanceâ” sir james replied,  â‘o really,  oh dragoâ”.  drago lifted sir james off the ground,  to the top of a cliff,  burnt the docks,  leaving king phillip begging for mercy,  sir james went to see title: Point of View
author: faith
text: no one could ever like me,  i'm too fat and ugly,  i'm stupid,  i'm clumsy.  chances are that i just make a fool of myself and no one could ever like me.   look at that girl,  over there,  i know her name,  and her life story,  everything she's ever done just shines with such glory,  she may not think anything good of herself,  but i love that girl right over there.   i'm just a bystander,  eyewitness,  yes,  and what's going on there,  none on earth could missguess.  he's in love with her,  she thinks she hasn't a prayer,  but he's in love with that girl over there.  some say that it's plain; she's no self-esteem,  could never be princess,  could never be queen.  to the world she's one person,  but to them she's the world,  i can't wait to see this come unfurled.  and you could know everything,  or not a bit,  because here is a truth that so few will admit,  this is hard for the girl and the boy to construe,  but it's all in the point of your view.  you could be miserable,  or you could be the best,  the average,  the loser,  the star,  and the rest.  so whenever you think the worst person is you,  it's all in the point of your view.
